 equipment and cumbersome geometric calibration. Experimental results using both synthetic and real-world data demonstrate that our Spectral MVIR can acquire a high-quality 3D model with accurate spectral reflectance property.\nCandidate Topics: iterative reconstruction, computer vision, rendering, photometry, rgb color model, photometric stereo, projector, image formation, artificial intelligence, solid modeling, 3d reconstruction, computer graphics images, image based modeling and rendering, shading, computational photography, visualization, pixel, pose, reflection mapping, epipolar geometry, image resolution, monocular, algorithm, compositing, projection, object, property, image restoration, image sensor, stereopsis, light field, dual, reconstruction algorithm, process, computer graphics, cone tracing, alpha compositing, structured light, building model, image based lighting, image, representation, 2d to 3d conversion, feature extraction, triangulation, global illumination, structure tensor, structure from motion, construct, photon mapping, calibration, transformation geometry, benchmark, camera auto calibration, decomposition, orthogonality, data modeling, subspace topology, lambertian reflectance, principle of compositionality, computational geometry, image fusion, shader, rendering equation, likelihood function, stereo camera, data visualization, task, image registration, image processing, trifocal tensor, stereo display, face, pattern recognition, 3d rendering, video projector, solidity, robot, precomputed radiance transfer, interpolation, bilinear interpolation, computation, projection mapping, camera resectioning, skeletonization, standard illuminant, surrogate model, graphics, ray tracing, proxy, inpainting, luminance, digital light processing, kernel, unscented transform, null, generative model, fundamental matrix, metamorphic testing, radiosity"}], 'stream': False, 'seed': 347} failed after all attempts. Saving errors: [{'error': {'message': 'Budget has 