ments show our model is highly sample efficient: using a low-resource benchmark derived from TOPv2, our inventory parser outperforms a copy-generate parser by +15 EM absolute (44% relative) when fine-tuning on 10 samples from an unseen domain.\nCandidate Topics: ontology, parsing, natural language processing, bootstrapping, utterance, transformer, categorization, web ontology language, domain, categorical variable, ontology language, inference, python, ontology based data integration, bootstrapping, classifier, construct, machine learning, dependency grammar, treebank, upper ontology, cache, parse tree, semantic web stack, suggested upper merged ontology, tree, classifier, decision tree, container, ontology engineering, parser combinator, question answering, information retrieval, process ontology, natural language, ontology inference layer, semantic web, programming language, s attributed grammar, ontology learning, ontology merging, cluster analysis, timestamp, component, ontology alignment, xml, artificial neural network, crowdsourcing, data mining, semantics, oracle, incremental decision tree, phrase, top down parsing, data modeling, testbed, logistic regression, scalability, taxonomy, noun phrase, semantic computing, soap, heuristics, ontology components, dialog box, ontology concept, theoretical computer science, interpretation, deep learning, raw data, pairwise comparison, bottom up parsing, conceptual model, computational linguistics, owl s, generic bootstrapping architecture, dependency, test set, process, framing, supervised learning, proxy, discriminative model, conceptualization, web application, rdf, tree traversal, benchmark, probabilistic logic, annotation, e commerce, leverage, domain model, language model, lr parser, recommender system, conceptual model, crowdsourced testing, task, decision tree learning'}], 'stream': False, 'seed': 347} failed after all attempts. Saving errors: [{'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.42335