rience RETRO-VIZ as a useful tool to assess the trustworthiness of algorithmic predictions.\nCandidate Topics: machine learning, visualization, measure, regression analysis, data mining, data science, human computer interaction, data visualization, artificial intelligence, information retrieval, linear regression, data modeling, empirical modelling, interpretability, statistical model, recommender system, leverage, moderation, logistic regression, information visualization, ranking, variable, user modeling, conceptual model, interpretation, graphical model, control, explanation based learning, knowledge management, conceptual model, data analysis, structural equation modeling, visual analytics, interpretation, model selection, reliability, simple linear regression, advice, simulation, exploratory data analysis, correlation coefficient, analytics, ordinal regression, predictive modelling, baseline, proxy, relation, inference, effective method, visual reasoning, predictive analytics, empirical process, creative visualization, ranking, construct, software, variety, smoothing, linear model, relevance, spurious relationship, performance prediction, graph, multimedia, model based reasoning, factor analysis, natural language processing, usability, missing data, world wide web, crowdsourcing, factor, estimation theory, text mining, link analysis, reduction, misinformation, rank, heuristic, advice, structured prediction, variation, documentation, multilevel model, latent variable model, set, lag, benchmark, main effect, learning to rank, selection, imputation, thesaurus, bootstrapping, simple, decision support system, data point, variables, granger causality, computer mediated communication'}], 'stream': False, 'seed': 347} failed after all attempts. Saving errors: [{'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'type': 'budget_exceeded', 'param': None, 'code': '400'}}, {'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Curr