 NLP tools. Yet state-of-the-art models did offer significant gains. The best approach we investigated combined domain-matched pretraining, sound pooling, and state-of-the-art deep transformer network encoders. Finally, with the goal of leveraging contextual representations from deep encoders, we present a range of measurements for understanding and forecasting research communities in science.\nCandidate Topics: natural language processing, transformer, text mining, word embedding, encoder, natural language understanding, embedding, biomedical text mining, natural language, machine learning, text processing, text corpus, inference, word, sentiment analysis, machine translation, information extraction, automatic summarization, tweaking, textual entailment, pooling, sentence, language model, data mining, deep learning, information retrieval, artificial neural network, question answering, text graph, noisy text analytics, formal verification, recurrent neural network, predictive text, semeval, speech recognition, structured text, data science, encoding, feature engineering, computational linguistics, feature, human computer interaction, document classification, feature extraction, artificial intelligence, emerging technologies, relationship extraction, representation, formal language, hidden markov model, semantic analysis, encryption, rich text format, key, convolutional neural network, world wide web, keyword extraction, interpretability, knowledge extraction, cohesion, field, reverse engineering, abstraction layer, text segmentation, pairwise comparison, software engineering, isolation, text retrieval conference, theoretical computer science, feature learning, transcription, unified medical language system, sentence extraction, transmission, automated mining, computational neuroscience, text normalization, analytics, latent semantic analysis, autoencoder, phrase, translation, social media, embedded system, ontology, intellectual property, multi document summarizatio