ERROR:root:Request {'model': 'protected.gpt-4.1-mini', 'messages': [{'role': 'system', 'content': "\n    You will receive a paper abstract along with a set of candidate topics for the paper. \n    Your first task is to select the topics that best align with the core theme of the paper.\n    Exclude topics that are too broad or less relevant. \n    Only use the topic names in the candidate set. \n    Your second task is to generate a complete list of key phrases extracted from the paper.\n    Do some rationalization before outputting the list of relevant topics and key phrases.\n    Output format: '<top> topic 1, topic 2, ... </top><kp>key phrase 1, key phrase 2, ... </kp>'.\n    "}, {'role': 'user', 'content': 'Title: \nPaper Abstract: Augmented World Models Facilitate Zero-Shot Dynamics Generalization From a Single Offline Environment. Reinforcement learning from large-scale offline datasets provides us with the ability to learn policies without potentially unsafe or impractical exploration. Significant progress has been made in the past few years in dealing with the challenge of correcting for differing behavior between the data collection and learned policies. However, little attention has been paid to potentially changing dynamics when transferring a policy to the online setting, where performance can be up to 90% reduced for existing methods. In this paper we address this problem with Augmented World Models (AugWM). We augment a learned dynamics model with simple transformations that seek to capture potential changes in physical properties of the robot, leading to more robust policies. We not only train our policy in this new setting, but also provide it with the sampled augmentation as a context, allowing it to adapt to changes in the environment. At test time we learn the context in a self-supervised fashion by approximating the augmentation which corresponds to the new environment. We rigorously evaluate our approach on over 100 different changed dynamics settings, and show that this simple approach can significantly improve the zero-shot generalization of a recent state-of-the-art baseline, often achieving successful policies where the baseline fails.\nCandidate Topics: baseline, robot, reinforcement learning, artificial intelligence, machine learning, robustness, robot learning, robot kinematics, data modeling, shot, artificial neural network, robotics, deep learning, cold start, visualization, human computer interaction, one shot learning, benchmark, key, simple, object, heuristic, feature extraction, ground truth, humanoid robot, leverage, leabra, synthetic data, normalization, grasp, feature learning, variety, data mining, semantics, human robot interaction, categorization, task, autonomous agent, entropy, noise, stability, motion, data model, autonomous robot, hazard, heuristics, threat model, adaptation, algorithmic learning theory, reduction, mobile robot, unsupervised learning, online machine learning, hue, proactive learning, reliability, recurrent neural network, semi supervised learning, embedding, transfer of learning, heuristic, algorithm, behavior based robotics, feature, scheme, evolutionary robotics, robotic paradigms, black box, cognitive robotics, hidden markov model, statistical relational learning, control, alpha, dropout, focus, backup, probabilistic logic, intrinsics, hyper heuristic, supervised learning, robot calibration, reset, soar, dynamic programming, cut, social robot, code, block, consistency, raw data, planner, robot end effector, state, calibration, motion planning, cyber physical system, simulation, computer vision, gloh, data science'}], 'stream': False, 'seed': 347} failed after all attempts. Saving errors: [{'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'type': 'budget_exceeded', 'param': None, 'code': '400'}}, {'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'type': 'budget_excee