 of Weka software, the data was normalized and the normalized data was used as a learning set. As a result of the examinations, a decision tree (J48) algorithm with the highest accuracy was chosen and an artificial intelligence model was created. Decisions are used to manage operations such as starting, maintaining and stopping the irrigation. The accuracy of the decisions was evaluated and the irrigation system was tested with the results. There are options to manage, view the system remotely and manually and also see the system s decisions with the created mobile application.\nCandidate Topics: process, software, decision tree, field, simulation, set, data mining, mobile computing, machine learning, embedded system, artificial neural network, application software, real time computing, database, artificial intelligence, mobile device, c4 5 algorithm, computer engineering, statistical classification, variable, tree, random forest, process control, decision tree learning, goto, mouseover, use case, wizard, ubiquitous computing, key, feature extraction, standard cell, simple, decision support system, statistical process control, sdet, computer go, bokeh, decision tree model, statistical model, factory, deep learning, polling, data analysis, data processing, kernel, information technology, control, wireless, koorde, decision engineering, emi, process variable, computer hardware, decision model, wireless sensor network, entropy, tera, distributed computing, multivariate statistics, bluetooth, python, drmaa, value, firmware, measure, data science, cluster analysis, data set, web application, ibeacon, microcontroller, rough set, intelligent decision support system, md5, mobile phone, component, computer network, layer, init, process variation, kernel, software engineering, minifloat, telecommunications, information management, standardization, mobile technology, imt advanced, microsoft office, ticket, computation, state, chipset, decision rule, rust, headset, netflow, dec