ERROR:root:Request {'model': 'protected.gpt-4.1-mini', 'messages': [{'role': 'system', 'content': "\n    You will receive a paper abstract along with a set of candidate topics for the paper. \n    Your first task is to select the topics that best align with the core theme of the paper.\n    Exclude topics that are too broad or less relevant. \n    Only use the topic names in the candidate set. \n    Your second task is to generate a complete list of key phrases extracted from the paper.\n    Do some rationalization before outputting the list of relevant topics and key phrases.\n    Output format: '<top> topic 1, topic 2, ... </top><kp>key phrase 1, key phrase 2, ... </kp>'.\n    "}, {'role': 'user', 'content': 'Title: \nPaper Abstract: SRA-LSTM: Social Relationship Attention LSTM for Human Trajectory Prediction. Pedestrian trajectory prediction for surveillance video is one of the important research topics in the field of computer vision and a key technology of intelligent surveillance systems. Social relationship among pedestrians is a key factor influencing pedestrian walking patterns but was mostly ignored in the literature. Pedestrians with different social relationships play different roles in the motion decision of target pedestrian. Motivated by this idea, we propose a Social Relationship Attention LSTM (SRA-LSTM) model to predict future trajectories. We design a social relationship encoder to obtain the representation of their social relationship through the relative position between each pair of pedestrians. Afterwards, the social relationship feature and latent movements are adopted to acquire the social relationship attention of this pair of pedestrians. Social interaction modeling is achieved by utilizing social relationship attention to aggregate movement information from neighbor pedestrians. Experimental results on two public walking pedestrian video datasets (ETH and UCY), our model achieves superior performance compared with state-of-the-art methods. Contrast experiments with other attention methods also demonstrate the effectiveness of social relationship attention.\nCandidate Topics: key, field, aggregate, machine learning, feature, artificial intelligence, contrast, representation, feature extraction, human computer interaction, feature, ubiquitous computing, salient, baseline, factor, frame, representation, artificial neural network, feature learning, measure, focus, motion, mobile computing, perspective, social network, social computing, data science, deep learning, inference, frame, contextual image classification, fidelity, key frame, signal, similarity, feature model, data mining, data modeling, visualization, classifier, association, relation, social media, multi agent system, statistical model, semantics, natural language processing, support vector machine, embedding, social dynamics, pattern recognition, leverage, event, intelligent decision support system, recurrent neural network, structure from motion, social learning, alpha, cohesion, contrast, hidden markov model, process, computer vision, transfer of learning, conditional random field, dual, wearable computer, feature vector, multimedia, activity recognition, feature engineering, face, human dynamics, transfer, autoencoder, knowledge management, state, social system, margin, encoding, joint, sample, encoder, embodied cognition, speech recognition, pattern recognition, human visual system model, constant, similarity measure, coupling, language model, sensor fusion, pooling, collective intelligence, image fusion, classifier, information retrieval, human robot interaction, construct, spatial contextual awareness'}], 'stream': False, 'seed': 347} failed after all attempts. Saving errors: [{'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'type': 'budget_exceeded', 'param': None, 'code': '400'}}, {'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'typ