es the potential for trajectory prediction in real-world traffic.\nCandidate Topics: semantic mapping, graph, machine learning, dynamic network analysis, data mining, semantics, artificial intelligence, task, semantic network, real time computing, dynamic programming, visualization, robot, dynamic data, semantics, semantic data model, simultaneous localization and mapping, key, network mapping, mobile robot, data modeling, cluster analysis, topological map, semantic grid, semantic analysis, mobile computing, routing, feature extraction, semantic computing, matching, map matching, global map, deep learning, robustness, theoretical computer science, entropy, distributed computing, motion planning, graph partition, artificial neural network, semantic technology, directed graph, semantic web, hidden markov model, motion, global positioning system, big data, dynamic bayesian network, reliability, simulation, mobile mapping, reverse semantic traceability, dynamic dispatch, categorization, process, dynamic simulation, semantic integration, probabilistic latent semantic analysis, scheduling, dynamic time warping, match moving, semantic similarity, data mapping, computer vision, network topology, metrical task system, pose, dynamic problem, heterogeneous network, dynamic priority scheduling, traffic generation model, benchmark, occupancy grid mapping, set, abstract semantic graph, tracking, dual, software, static routing, algorithm design, mobile robot navigation, pattern recognition, collaborative mapping, graph database, control flow graph, embedding, data stream mining, depth map, vehicle routing problem, representation, traffic analysis, robotic mapping, face, semantic feature, transfer, state, temporal database, semantic gap, video tracking, object"}], 'stream': False, 'seed': 347} failed after all attempts. Saving errors: [{'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'type': 'budget_exceeded', 'param': None, 'code'