ERROR:root:Request {'model': 'protected.gpt-4.1-mini', 'messages': [{'role': 'system', 'content': "\n    You will receive a paper abstract along with a set of candidate topics for the paper. \n    Your first task is to select the topics that best align with the core theme of the paper.\n    Exclude topics that are too broad or less relevant. \n    Only use the topic names in the candidate set. \n    Your second task is to generate a complete list of key phrases extracted from the paper.\n    Do some rationalization before outputting the list of relevant topics and key phrases.\n    Output format: '<top> topic 1, topic 2, ... </top><kp>key phrase 1, key phrase 2, ... </kp>'.\n    "}, {'role': 'user', 'content': 'Title: \nPaper Abstract: Augmenting Automated Game Testing with Deep Reinforcement Learning. General game testing relies on the use of human play testers, play test scripting, and prior knowledge of areas of interest to produce relevant test data. Using deep reinforcement learning (DRL), we introduce a self-learning mechanism to the game testing framework. With DRL, the framework is capable of exploring and/or exploiting the game mechanics based on a user-defined, reinforcing reward signal. As a result, test coverage is increased and unintended game play mechanics, exploits and bugs are discovered in a multitude of game types. In this paper, we show that DRL can be used to increase test coverage, find exploits, test map difficulty, and to detect common problems that arise in the testing of first-person shooter (FPS) games.\nCandidate Topics: game testing, reinforcement learning, code coverage, test data generation, game mechanics, human computer interaction, metamorphic testing, scripting language, test data, game design, video game, code, deep learning, machine learning, test harness, test strategy, artificial intelligence, video game design, exploit, fuzz testing, video game development, use case, test set, system testing, software, multimedia, computer game, software bug, code generation, turing test, test management approach, game design document, cover, keyword driven testing, game developer, behavior based robotics, robot learning, white box testing, source code, benchmark, nesting, real time testing, leverage, level design, game development tool, grammar based code, natural language, simulator sickness, game art design, behavioral pattern, loop, simulation, signal, chess endgame, software performance testing, construct, manual testing, game programming, software engineering, trainer, emergent gameplay, web testing, dynamic testing, task, behavioral targeting, motion, unit testing, thesaurus, human behavior, driving simulator, turns rounds and time keeping systems in games, test driven development, domain knowledge, noise, morse code, game complexity, generative grammar, covering code, human in the loop, cross site scripting, usability, sequence learning, game physics, stereotaxy, strategy pattern, robot, debugging, block, modular design, computer architecture, tone, heuristics, graphical user interface testing, state, software quality, test double, performance tuning, vetting, virtual training, tree testing'}], 'stream': False, 'seed': 347} failed after all attempts. Saving errors: [{'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'type': 'budget_exceeded', 'param': None, 'code': '400'}}, {'error': {'message': 'HTTP 200: JSON `null` body (upstream/proxy glitch; not a valid chat completion)', 'type': 'empty_body'}}, {'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'type': 'budget_exceeded', 'param': None, 'code': '400'}}, {'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'type': 'budget_exceeded', 'param': None, 'code': '400'}}, {'error': {'message': 'Budget has been exceeded! Current cost: 5.423352675000006, Max budget: 5.0', 'type': 'budget_exceeded', 'param': No